low.ts -> src/domain/billing.ts -> src/presentation/invoice-view.ts -> src/application/billing-flow.ts`\\n\\nBreaking the domain-to-presentation import is the most important architectural fix because it likely removes one leg of the cycle while restoring the intended dependency direction.\\n\\n`layer_violation` and `deep_import` differ in agent risk:\\n\\n- `layer_violation` is about internal architecture drift. It teaches future edits the wrong dependency direction, so an agent may keep pushing presentation concerns into domain code or make broad changes across layers to satisfy one import.\\n- `deep_import` is about package surface instability. It may work today, but an agent will treat private package internals as stable API, making upgrades brittle and failures harder to predict.\\n\\nSo: break `src/domain/billing.ts -> src/presentation/invoice-view.ts`; redirect that collaboration through a domain-owned interface wired by application code. Replace `some-pkg/dist/internal/private/helper.js` with a public package entry or isolate it behind an adapter until a public API exists.\"}}\n{\"type\":\"turn.completed\",\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":18275,\"cached_input_tokens\":11136,\"output_tokens\":635,\"reasoning_output_tokens\":65}}\n",
