een those two runs is the actual bug — likely a period/proration calculation that uses \"now\" twice and crosses a day boundary between the two reads.\n\n3. **Assert the boundary explicitly.** Add a regression test that fixes the clock at the exact rollover moment and asserts the expected invoice/period shape. This turns a flaky test into a deterministic one and protects against the next agent reintroducing a direct `Date.now()` call.\n\nLower-priority but worth bundling: delete the commented-out `legacyRefund` block (`crime_00003`, lines 33–37) and the zero-assert test (`crime_00006`) while you're in the file — both will mislead the next agent debugging this area.",
