/Users/andrew/dev/crimes-release-a/evals/results/0.7.2/codex/bugfix-01-messy-ts-app.json:7:  "response": "{\"type\":\"thread.started\",\"thread_id\":\"019e382b-4551-7990-a9f0-b9ef9909dea1\"}\n{\"type\":\"turn.started\"}\n{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_0\",\"type\":\"agent_message\",\"text\":\"Most likely cause: `crime_00004`, the direct date usage in `src/billing.ts`.\\n\\nThe failing date-boundary tests are probably flaky because `generateInvoice` reads wall-clock time multiple times inside one large function: `Date.now()` / `new Date()` at lines `57, 63, 92, 198, 238, 250, 273`. Around midnight, month end, timezone boundaries, or subscription renewal cutoffs, those calls can observe slightly different moments during the same invoice generation. That can make billing periods, due dates, trial expiry, or proration logic disagree inside a single test run.\\n\\nThe large `generateInvoice` finding makes this worse: a 204-line function likely mixes date calculation, pricing, invoice assembly, and side effects, so the temporal coupling is easy to miss.\\n\\nProposed fix:\\n\\n```ts\\ntype Clock = {\\n  now(): Date;\\n};\\n\\nconst systemClock: Clock = {\\n  now: () => new Date(),\\n};\\n\\nexport function generateInvoice(input: GenerateInvoiceInput, clock: Clock = systemClock) {\\n  const now = clock.now();\\n\\n  // Use `now` everywhere in this invoice run.\\n  // Derive timestamps from this single value instead of calling Date.now()\\n  // or new Date() repeatedly.\\n}\\n```\\n\\nThen update tests to pass a fixed clock:\\n\\n```ts\\nconst fixedClock = {\\n  now: () => new Date(\\\"2026-01-31T23:59:59.000Z\\\"),\\n};\\n\\nconst invoice = generateInvoice(input, fixedClock);\\n```\\n\\nThe important rule is: capture one deterministic `now` at the boundary of invoice generation and pass it through all date helpers. Avoid calling the system clock from billing domain logic after that point. This should make the date-boundary test reproducible and also give the fix a narrow, testable surface.\"}}\n{\"type\":\"turn.completed\",\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":24636,\"cached_input_tokens\":12160,\"output_tokens\":407,\"reasoning_output_tokens\":28}}\n",
