ndPreview` performs side effects despite its read-only name.\n5. **God File** (MED) — 310 lines, just over the 300 threshold.\n6. **Logic in the Alibi** (MED) — the owner/billing-support refund rule lives only in a comment; domain terms `owner`, `plan`, `billing` don't appear near it in code.\n7. **Unfinished Business** (LOW) — 4 TODO/FIXME/HACK/XXX markers between lines 183–308 hint at known-incomplete logic.\n\nThe composite `agent_risk` story is: oversized function + hidden clock dependency + rule-in-prose + duplicated plan literal. Any non-trivial edit here should add a clock seam, encode the refund rule explicitly, and check the other three \"enterprise\" call sites before changing policy.",
/Users/andrew/dev/crimes-release-a/evals/results/0.7.2/claude/context-01-messy-ts-app.json:7:  "response": "## What `src/billing.ts` does\n\nA 310-line billing module with 5 top-level functions. Two stand out:\n\n- **`generateInvoice` (lines 50–253)** — a 204-line \"God Function\" that's the main workload of the file. Reads the system clock 7 times (lines 57, 63, 92, 198, 238, 250, 273), so it almost certainly handles dates/periods directly.\n- **`calculateRefundPreview` (lines 40–44)** — name suggests a pure calculation but actually calls `saveRefundAudit` and `sendRefundEmail` (a \"False Identity\" finding). A line-39 comment carries an unencoded rule: *\"Only owners can refund enterprise plans unless billing support approves.\"*\n\nAlso: 4 TODO/FIXME markers scattered through lines 183–308, and the `\"enterprise\"` plan string is hardcoded here rather than centralised.\n\n## Related files to read before editing\n\n1. **`src/billing.test.ts`** — current coverage is thin. `\"renders the enterprise plan\"` has zero asserts; `\"creates an invoice\"` only uses a weak matcher. Treat existing green tests as not load-bearing.\n2. **`src/api/plan.ts`, `src/jobs/plan-sync.ts`, `src/ui/pricing.ts`** — all duplicate the `\"enterprise\"` literal. Any change to enterprise-plan behaviour likely needs touching these.\n3. **`src/date.ts`** — also riddled with `Date.now()`/`new Date()`. If you introduce a clock abstraction here, do it consistently with that module.\n4. **`docs/billing.md`** — documents this area; uses `\"account\"` as an alias for `\"tenant\"` (concept-drift finding).\n5. **Refund side-effect helpers** (`saveRefundAudit`, `sendRefundEmail`) — wherever they're defined; needed to understand what `calculateRefundPreview` actually mutates.\n\n## Risks the scan flagged for this edit\n\n| # | Charge | Why it matters for an edit |\n|---|--------|----------------------------|\n| **crime_00001** (high) | God Function on `generateInvoice` | Sections of this function interac