/Users/andrew/dev/crimes-release-a/evals/results/0.7.2-judge/claude/bugfix-08-stress-dependency.json:7:  "response": "## Break: `src/domain/billing.ts` → `src/presentation/invoice-view.ts`\n\nThat single import is the root cause. Removing it both breaks the cycle and fixes the layer violation in one move.\n\n**Why this edge and not the others**\n\nThe three files form a ring. Two of the three edges are architecturally legitimate:\n\n- `presentation/invoice-view.ts` → `application/billing-flow.ts` — presentation calling into application is the normal direction.\n- `application/billing-flow.ts` → `domain/billing.ts` — application calling into domain is the normal direction.\n- `domain/billing.ts` → `presentation/invoice-view.ts` — **wrong direction**. Domain reaching into presentation inverts the dependency flow and is what `crime_00002` flags (`rule: domain cannotImport presentation`).\n\n`crime_00001` (the cycle) and `crime_00002` (the layer violation) share the same offending edge. Fix it once, both findings go away.\n\n**How to break it**\n\nThe suggested action on `crime_00001` lists two mechanical options; pick based on what `domain/billing.ts` is actually using from `invoice-view.ts`:\n\n1. **If it imports a type only** — change to `import type { ... } from '../presentation/invoice-view'`. Type-only imports are erased at compile time and don't contribute a runtime edge, so the cycle disappears without moving any code. Cheapest fix.\n2. **If it imports a value (function, class, constant)** — that's a real dependency in the wrong direction. Extract the shared piece (types, a formatter helper, whatever it actually needs) into a third module under `domain/` or a neutral `shared/` location, and have both `domain/billing.ts` and `presentation/invoice-view.ts` import from it. Don't relax the layer rule to make the import legal; the rule is correct.\n\n**What to check before editing**\n\nOpen `src/domain/billing.ts` and look at what it imports from `invoice-view.ts`. That determines which of the two fixes applies. `crime_00003` (deep import in `billing-flow.ts`) is unrelated to the cycle and can be addressed separately.",
