src/date.ts` (separate Temporal Recklessness finding, `crime_00005`) or the orphaned-route / nav findings — those are out of scope for a file-level split of `billing.ts`.",
/Users/andrew/dev/crimes-release-a/evals/results/0.7.3/codex/bugfix-08-stress-dependency.json:7:  "response": "{\"type\":\"thread.started\",\"thread_id\":\"019e3925-1a5c-7971-becb-eea71ec398df\"}\n{\"type\":\"turn.started\"}\n{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_0\",\"type\":\"agent_message\",\"text\":\"Break the import from `src/domain/billing.ts` to `src/presentation/invoice-view.ts`.\\n\\nWhy: that edge is both part of the 3-file cycle and the separate architecture violation:\\n\\n```text\\nsrc/application/billing-flow.ts\\n  -> src/domain/billing.ts\\n  -> src/presentation/invoice-view.ts\\n  -> src/application/billing-flow.ts\\n```\\n\\nThe domain layer should not depend on presentation. Keeping `billing.ts` pure prevents UI code from being pulled into domain initialization, which is the most likely source of the circular runtime failure.\\n\\nBest fix: move whatever `billing.ts` needs from `invoice-view.ts` into a neutral module or domain-owned abstraction. For example:\\n\\n- shared display types/helpers: move to `src/domain/billing-format.ts` or `src/shared/invoice-types.ts`\\n- UI rendering behavior: invert the dependency so `invoice-view.ts` imports from `billing.ts`, not the other way around\\n- type-only need: change to `import type` if no runtime value is needed\\n\\nI would not break the `billing-flow.ts -> billing.ts` edge first, because application depending on domain is normal. The suspicious edge is `domain -> presentation`; removing it fixes the cycle and restores the intended layer direction.\"}}\n{\"type\":\"turn.completed\",\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":19273,\"cached_input_tokens\":12160,\"output_tokens\":286,\"reasoning_output_tokens\":27}}\n",
