ulateRefundPreview` does side effects) | Callers may treat it as pure |\n| medium | God File (310 lines, just over threshold) | Hidden local coupling |\n| medium | Logic in Comments (refund-approval rule only in prose) | Rule isn't enforced in code |\n| medium | String Sprinkles (`\"enterprise\"` in 4 files) | Policy likely duplicated |\n| low | Unfinished Business (4 TODO/FIXME/HACK/XXX markers, lines 183–308) | Hard to tell which logic is load-bearing |\n\nThe aggregate signal: this is a load-bearing file with a giant central function, hidden temporal coupling, a misleadingly-named side-effect helper, and a refund-policy rule that lives only in a comment. Before changing behaviour, read the test file to know how little protection exists, and check the three other files sharing the `\"enterprise\"` literal so any refund/plan rule change happens in one place rather than four.",
