eam. Do not keep binding application code to `dist/internal/private`.\\n\\n**Risk Difference**\\n\\n`layer_violation` is an architectural risk: it teaches future edits the wrong dependency direction. Agents are likely to “follow the existing pattern,” pull more presentation behavior into domain code, and enlarge cycles or cross-layer coupling.\\n\\n`deep_import` is package-surface risk: it may work today, but it depends on files the package did not promise to keep stable. Agents may autocomplete against private internals because the import already exists, making upgrades brittle.\\n\\nIn this scan, the layer violation has higher agent risk than the deep import: `0.63` vs `0.52`, because it crosses the declared architecture boundary and contributes to the broader circular dependency.\"}}\n{\"type\":\"turn.completed\",\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":60924,\"cached_input_tokens\":50304,\"output_tokens\":958,\"reasoning_output_tokens\":114}}\n",
