n SVG)\n- **IA**: #5 (missing AGENTS.md / CLAUDE.md)\n- **hot-path / portability** (not one of the five buckets — flagging): #4, #6, #7, #8\n- **testability** (also outside the five buckets): #10 (defer)\n- **git-history / duplication**: nothing in the top 10 — churn scores are all 0 (no git history on the fixture), and the duplication-adjacent findings (magic literals, nav source dup, route metadata drift) sit at #11+.\n\n## Why this order\n\nThe first three are real `severity: high` items with high confidence — fix them first. After that, `date.ts` is the single highest-leverage file: #2, #4, #8 are one refactor (inject a clock + pick a date library + format with explicit zone), so they get bundled. The portability pair (#6, #7) is trivial and gates every non-author machine, so it's cheap to do now rather than defer. #5 is the only \"fix now\" that isn't about code correctness — it's there because every later agent-assisted fix in this list gets cheaper once `AGENTS.md` exists. #9 and #10 are deferred not because they don't matter, but because doing them before #1 wastes work.\n\nNothing in the top 10 warrants **ignore** — the lowest-ranked here is still `medium` and has a concrete cheap fix.",
