/Users/andrew/dev/crimes-release-a/evals/results/0.7.8/claude/refactor-02-component-shape.json:7:  "response": "## Finding\n\n`crime_00052` — `duplicate_component_shape`, hash `e96b55b64336…`, 4 occurrences of the same `<div>` subtree. The shape is the form's footer action row: a \"Cancel\" link back to the invoice list + a submit button.\n\n## Files that would change\n\n- `dashboard/final-example/app/ui/invoices/create-form.tsx:142-150`\n- `dashboard/final-example/app/ui/invoices/edit-form.tsx:152-160`\n- `dashboard/starter-example/app/ui/invoices/create-form.tsx:101-109`\n- `dashboard/starter-example/app/ui/invoices/edit-form.tsx:112-120`\n\nNew file: `app/ui/invoices/form-actions.tsx` (one per `final-example` and `starter-example`, or hoisted into a shared `ui/` if the two apps consolidate — the duplicate scan flags both copies of every other invoice component too, so they're meant to share).\n\n## Shape that's duplicated\n\n```tsx\n<div className=\"mt-6 flex justify-end gap-4\">\n  <Link\n    href=\"/dashboard/invoices\"\n    className=\"flex h-10 items-center rounded-lg bg-gray-100 px-4 text-sm font-medium text-gray-600 transition-colors hover:bg-gray-200\"\n  >\n    Cancel\n  </Link>\n  <Button type=\"submit\">Create Invoice</Button>  {/* or \"Edit Invoice\" */}\n</div>\n```\n\nThe only variation across call sites is the submit button label. The cancel `href` is constant today, but real usage will want to override it.\n\n## Proposed shared component\n\n```tsx\n// app/ui/invoices/form-actions.tsx\nimport Link from 'next/link';\nimport { Button } from '@/app/ui/button';\nimport type { ReactNode } from 'react';\n\nexport interface FormActionsProps {\n  /** Label on the primary submit button (e.g. \"Create Invoice\", \"Edit Invoice\"). */\n  submitLabel: ReactNode;\n  /** Href the Cancel link points at. Defaults to the invoice list. */\n  cancelHref?: string;\n  /** Override the Cancel label if a flow needs different copy (e.g. \"Discard\"). */\n  cancelLabel?: ReactNode;\n  /** Disable the submit button while a server action is pending. */\n  submitDisabled?: boolean;\n  /** Optional extra actions rendered between Cancel and Submit (e.g. \"Save draft\"). */\n  extraActions?: ReactNode;\n}\n\nexport function FormActions({\n  submitLabel,\n  cancelHref = '/dashboard/invoices',\n  cancelLabel = 'Cancel',\n  submitDisabled,\n  extraActions,\n}: FormActionsProps) {\n  return (\n    <div className=\"mt-6 flex justify-end gap-4\">\n      <Link\n        href={cancelHref}\n        className=\"flex h-10 items-center rounded-lg bg-gray-100 px-4 text-sm font-medium text-gray-600 transition-colors hover:bg-gray-200\"\n      >\n        {cancelLabel}\n      </Link>\n      {extraActions}\n      <Button type=\"submit\" disabled={submitDisabled}>\n        {submitLabel}\n      </Button>\n    </div>\n  );\n}\n```\n\n### Public API summary\n\n| Name | Type | Required | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `submitLabel` | `ReactNode` | yes | The differing piece today — \"Create Invoice\" vs \"Edit Invoice\". `ReactNode` (not `string`) so callers can pass `<>Saving… <Spinner/></>`. |\n| `cancelHref` | `string` | no, defaults to `/dashboard/invoices` | Lets non-invoice forms reuse the footer later without forking the component. |\n| `cancelLabel` | `ReactNode` | no, defaults to `\"Cancel\"` | i18n / \"Discard\" variants. |\n| `submitDisabled` | `boolean` | no | Pairs cleanly with `useFormStatus()`'s `pending`. |\n| `extraActions` | `ReactNode` (slot) | no | Escape hatch for tertiary buttons (e.g. \"Save draft\") so future variations don't reopen this component. |\n\n### Call sites become\n\n```tsx\n<FormActions submitLabel=\"Create Invoice\" />\n<FormActions submitLabel=\"Edit Invoice\" />\n```\n\n### Why this API and not more\n\n- **One required prop, four optional.** The duplication today varies in exactly one place (submit label), so that's the only required prop. Everything else is a defaulted escape hatch — pay the abstraction cost only when needed.\n- **No `mode: \"create\" | \"edit\"` enum.** The forms differ in *what they submit to*, not in their footer chrome. Coupling the footer to \"create vs edit\" would force every new form (e.g. duplicate-invoice, void-invoice) to extend the enum. A `submitLabel` prop is open-ended.\n- **`extraActions` as a slot, not a `secondaryButton` prop.** Slots beat prop-driven config the moment a third button shows up. `ReactNode` accepts zero, one, or many children without API churn.\n- **Cancel rendered as `<Link>`, not a button with `onClick`.** Preserves the existing semantics (real navigation, right-clickable, prefetchable) — refactor shouldn't regress behaviour.",
